Sentencas: Current collection/interconnection of novel tubular solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is achieved by means of alloy metal interconnects based on Ducrolloy (Cr5Fe1Y(2)O(3)) coated with various electronically conductive coatings.
Titulo: Current collectors for a novel tubular design of solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Coatings applied to the metal interconnect improve cell performance.
Titulo: Current collectors for a novel tubular design of solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: For example, at 900 degrees C in air, a Ag-La0.8Sr0.2CrO3 (Ag-LSC) coated interconnect is used in conjunction with an 8 mol% yttria stabilised zirconia (YSZ) tubular electrolyte based SOFC.
Titulo: Current collectors for a novel tubular design of solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: At 0.7 V a cell performance of 40 mA/cm(2) is achieved for the coated sample, compared with a lower performance of 16 mA/cm(2) attained with an uncoated interconnect.
Titulo: Current collectors for a novel tubular design of solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The thermal shock resistant properties of the tubes are not compromised by use of the metal interconnect.
Titulo: Current collectors for a novel tubular design of solid oxide fuel cell
